Author:
Vol / Page: 10
Edition:
Quote: Jerry O'Dwyer had shot two crows from the new sniper's pozzy down at the creek. [Note: Pozzy or Possie - Australian warrior's short for "position", or lair. <i>Ibid.</i> 125 "Possie!" exclaimed the enquiring general. "What is a 'Possie'?" "That, sir," said the C.o., "is Australian for recess, either firing or sleeping. It's a contraction of 'position.".
